1) We need to set global variables for git, for every commit this is necessary
      git config --global user.name "codechaitu"
      git config --global user.email "codechaitu@mercari.com"
2) When we are not using global setting, then use config without the --global option
3)Configurations set till now -> git config --list
4.1) When we have contents already in a directory 
    a) git init
    b) git config user.name " "
    c) git config user.email " "
    d) git add *
    e) git add LICENSE
    f) git commit -m 'initial project version'
 4.2) When we need a directory from github
     a) git clone <url> ### same dirctory name after downloading 
     b) git clone <url> <user-specific-name> ### downloaded directory will be user-specific-name 
 5) To know the status of all files-> git status
 6) To know the differnce of files between newly edited version and ready to staged one (used git add already on that file) ->  git diff
 7) Commit the staged files -> git commit -m "message to commit"
